Text.Value: Death will be yours and yours alone, ghaik slave. Htak'a!
And you, Lae'zel - a child, an unascended - would snatch my glory for herself.
Mind flayers are our quarry. We have filled libraries with our knowledge of how to hunt them down.
Here you are, as brazen as described.
We tracked it from the moment the Astral Prism fell into its claws.
Vlaakith entrusted Lae'zel with the Prism. Interfere, and the queen's sure to punish you.
Orpheus lives. The empire will be his.

EditorData.logicalname: Githyanki - Laezel on Orpheus Path (For Approval)

Text.Value: And you - this child, this unascended - would snatch my glory for yourself.
Tsk'va. You faithless snake.
And now that we have found it, we will reclaim the Astral Prism, purge it of the illithid interloper, and restore it to its rightful owner.
The false heir's head will make a fine trophy for Vlaakith. As for you -
The traitor prince will be the fall of the githyanki.
My people answer to none but Gruumsh. We are merely allies.
I was not asking for it. Htak'a!
Have you quite forgotten what and who we are, kin?
Attack.
You should know the Emperor is not the only occupant of the Astral Prism.
It seems your report was good, W'wargaz.
Orpheus lives. The empire will be his.

EditorData.logicalname: Githyanki - Laezel on Vlaakith Path (For Approval)

Text.Value: Attack.
I'd give the artefact to you freely, but it isn't possible.
I serve none other than the wild tempest that is nature. We are merely allies.
I will liberate you from your puppet-master. Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith!

EditorData.NodeContext: Vlaakith's will above all! shouted as combat rally

Text.Value: It seems your report was good, W'wargaz. Glad you could join us, Lae'zel.
You cannot best me. You will die here, and your legacy will die with you.
Strike me and die - a failed warrior forgotten by our people.
Gith's wretched son will be the fall of the githyanki.
Vlaakith'ka sivim hrath krash'ht.

EditorData.NodeContext: Confidently, but not as a battle cry. VLAH-kith-kah SIV-im HRATH KRAHSH-het. Only in Vlaakith may we find light.

Text.Value: I thought you said this one was smart, W'wargaz?
This artefact contains the key to our freedom. It is not for the lich queen to take!
What are you doing?
You can certainly die trying.
I'd give it to you freely, if it were possible to do so.
I'll send you home in your own box!
The queen has entrusted me with the Prism. Interfere, and death will be her reward to you.
It seems your report was good, W'wargaz.
I'm told you carry an artefact most cherished.
You may keep your head. But I will yet be exalted. I will yet see my name carved in slate.
What honours, what riches, will the Undying Queen grant me when I hand her the failed prince?
Strike me and die, a failed warrior forgotten by your people.
I will deliver to her the Prince of the Comet. She shall exalt me. The gish will record my great deed in slate!
Dearest Lae'zel. You've fallen victim to a manipulation. The traitor prince would lead us to ruin.
More than our so-called 'queen' did.
An artefact our venerable queen would stop at nothing to take back.
I'd give the artefact to you freely, but it isn't possible.
The treacherous dragon-spawn who would steal from our queen.
The treacherous dark-dweller who would steal from our queen.
The traitor who would steal from our queen.
Your story ends here. We will reclaim the Astral Prism and restore it to our queen.
The kith'raki have spread word of that artefact that you carry.
Lae'zel. Glad you could join us.
Most illithids prefer to dominate their thralls through transformation, yet here you stand, untransformed.
Stand down - I protect the Prism on our queen's behalf!
I've fought stronger, faster, and more accomplished warriors than you. You cannot win.
Damnable whelp. For a thousand years have I given my life to Vlaakith.
Of course, you had help, didn't you? From the illithid you carry inside the Astral Prism.
This artefact contains our people's future. I won't let you take it.
How did you know about that?
What a pleasant surprise.
How quaint that we should meet here - in the very place that it once called home.
The promise of defeating the elder brain.
My dear child, I already know all there is to know.
Orpheus lives. The empire will be his.
Tell me, Lae'zel of K'liir. What reward do you think the Astral Prism will fetch once I pluck it from your corpse and present it to Vlaakith?
Your story ends here. We will reclaim the Astral Prism, purge it of the illithid interloper, and restore it to our queen.
Tell me - what did it offer you in exchange for your servitude?
The gloomed soul who thieved from our queen.
Stand down! It is on our Queen's sacred order that I keep the Prism close.
The queen has entrusted me with the Prism. Interfere, and death will be her only gift to you.
Ha! I see it keeps you on a tight leash. Very good.
There's no servitude - the illithid is my ally.
It seems your report was good, W'wargaz. Glad you could join us, Lae'zel.
You have fallen prey to its manipulation.
Lae'zel. Glad you could join us.
Stand down! It is on our queen's sacred order that I keep the Prism close.
I serve one far greater than any illithid. We are merely allies.
I'd give it to you freely, if the mind flayer would let me.
I will remember you said that.
I know exactly what the Prism contains. The traitor prince who would hand us to ghaik.
The queen has entrusted me with the Prism. Interfere, and death will be her reward to you.

Text.Value: All that matters is that it is delivered.
Vlaakith will not have your head today. But have it, she will.

Text.Value: My people served the illithid once - never again. We are allies.
The Undying Queen cares not for who delivers her the Prism and the traitor prince within.
Orpheus is the githyanki's true prince. You will not take him.
Strike me and die, a failed warrior forgotten by your people.
This artefact contains the key to our freedom. It is not for the lich queen to take!
Lae'zel. So you decided to make your appearance.
Orpheus lives. The empire will be his.
- I will leave nothing behind but meat and shattered bone.
We know all about the 'Emperor' and its dealings with you. Though I must confess its peculiar relationship with you threw us off course for a while.
Stand down - I protect the Prism on our queen's behalf!
And you would trust an illithid to do such a thing?
That's quite all right.
The gloomed soul who thieved from our queen.
Most illithids prefer to dominate their thralls through transformation, yet here you stand, only partially transformed.
Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith!
Orpheus is the githyanki's true prince. You will not take him.
